Official Dell distributor Drive Control Corporation (DCC) has introduced the Dell Optiplex 7070 Ultra, an innovative desktop that stores its small and powerful technology vertically inside a thin and light display stand. Available immediately to DCC’s SA and SADC channel partners, the Dell Optiplex 7070 Ultra offers a flexible, zero-footprint desktop design allowing for a working environment that is clutter free. The Optiplex 7070 Ultra is fully modular which means users can configure and upgrade it as needed throughout the product lifecycle. Comments George Lodewick, Dell Desktop and Notebook Specialist at DCC: “The independent upgradability of the Optiplex 7070 Ultra brings the best of the traditional desktop and the All-in-One together into a single, new, innovative platform that boost productivity while saving space – an important differentiator.” A recent Dell study shows that using two monitors can boost worker productivity by up to 21 percent. The Optiplex 7070 Ultra can support up to three displays – from 19 to 27 inches – for increased productivity. Power, data, video and audio are transmitted in one single cable when the Ultra is paired with Dell USB-C monitors. The Dell Optiplex 7070 Ultra offers the following key features: The Dell Optiplex 7070 Ultra ships with 3-year next business day warranty. Click here to know more. This article was published in partnership with DCC Dell.